==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Experientialism
<hw>Ex*pe`ri*en"tial*ism</hw>
<pr>(⟦ecr⟧ks*p⟦emac⟧`r⟦icr⟧*⟦ecr⟧n"sh⟦ait⟧l*⟦icr⟧z'm)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Philos.)</fld> <def>The doctrine that experience,
either that of ourselves or of others, is the test or criterion of
general knowledge; -- opposed to
<contr>intuitionalism</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Experientialism</qex> is in short, a philosophical or logical
theory, not a psychological one.</q> <rj><qau>G. C.
Robertson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Experientialist</ent>⟦br⟧
